01:04:48.970 --> 01:04:53.630
MOLLY SMITH: We look at it
holistically at Arena Stage.

01:04:53.630 --> 01:04:56.940
When I came to Arena, our
audience was not diverse

01:04:56.940 --> 01:05:00.430
so I walked the streets
of Washington, DC.

01:05:00.430 --> 01:05:03.370
I went into the churches
in Washington, DC.

01:05:03.370 --> 01:05:05.350
I went into some of
the Baptist churches

01:05:05.350 --> 01:05:08.720
and of course Washington DC
is a black and white city.

01:05:08.720 --> 01:05:14.470
And there was programming that we
had on stage that really focused

01:05:14.470 --> 01:05:16.060
on the African American experience,

01:05:16.060 --> 01:05:18.360
but our audiences didn't
reflect that.

01:05:18.360 --> 01:05:21.640
And this is unusual
because Arena started

01:05:21.640 --> 01:05:27.000
as the first integrated theater
in Washington, DC 68 years ago.

01:05:27.000 --> 01:05:30.910
And so it's in our bloodlines,
the importance of this.

01:05:30.910 --> 01:05:35.430
And so I realized it all happens
through programming and so

01:05:35.430 --> 01:05:37.630
about a third to half of the work

01:05:37.630 --> 01:05:41.150
that we do every year is
around people of color.

01:05:41.150 --> 01:05:42.690
When I was in the Baptist churches,

01:05:42.690 --> 01:05:47.110
I saw the way in which people
welcomed people is they would stand

01:05:47.110 --> 01:05:49.270
outside the door and shake hands

01:05:49.270 --> 01:05:51.740
with people all the
way into the church.

01:05:51.740 --> 01:05:53.710
So, we changed our usher structure.

01:05:53.710 --> 01:05:55.190
So, there are people all the way

01:05:55.190 --> 01:05:57.460
